      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T17:55:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "did you try running this query on real data? my reading of this query is that it is very slow.\nit requires reading all test results of an invocation (recursively) to return *the first page*.\nthis is because of the GROUP BY + HAVING - to group, you have to read everything.\n\nideally fetching the first page is O(test results in the first page), not O(test results in the invocation).\nI think it can be achieved with UnexpectedTestResults - it can replace the HAVING filter - if it doesn\u0027t join, then it is expected.",
      "revId": "85e98be92d1cabcdd4ecd95a9770a6efa438ae2b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
